                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>On the north wall of the central shrine in the Vālīśvara temple.</p>						
                            
                            <p>Ś. 1358: 1436 A.D.</p>						
                            
                            <p>The details of date <hi rend="italic">i.e.</hi>, Śaka 1338, Naḷa, Arpaśi, 25 are irregular. If the Śaka year quoted is a mistake for Ś. 1358, the date would correspond to 1436 A.D.</p>						
                            
                            <p>This inscription records the gift of two door-ways in the shrine of Tiruvālīśvaramuḍaiya nāyanār and the setting up of an image of Tiruppaḷḷi-nāchchiyār for the god, by Śakkaraśar, son of Ayyaluppi Kaḍaiyār Vide No. <ref target="DHARMA_INSSIIv17p0i0725">725</ref> below. </p>						
                            
                        </summary>
                    </msContents>
                    <physDesc>
                        <handDesc>
                            <p/>
                        </handDesc>
                    </physDesc>
                </msDesc>
